column3: Schedule - How to manage team schedules (i.e. clinics/grids) to meet patients' needs.
column4: New patients - How to get new patients in care, while meeting existing patients' needs.
column5: Return to clinic - How return to clinic orders free us to get patients' to the right treatment at the right time.
column6: Overwork - How overbooking or overworking increases patient no shows.
column7: Psychotherapy - How to improve team psychotherapy and patients' patterns of engagement.
column8: Evidence-based Psychotherapy - How to improve evidence-based psychotherapy in our team.
column9: Evidence-based Pharmacotherapy - How to improve evidence-based pharmacotherapy in our team.
column10: Referrals - How to manage referrals to our team and services (e.g., meds, therapy, group) within our team.
column11: Mix of services - How our patients engage in our team's mix of services.
column12: Improvement - Which improvements will have the best effects across our mix of services?
column13: Burnout - How to reduce provider burnout and improve patient satisfaction with care.
column14: Staffing - How to improve team care with our existing staff mix.
column15: Suicide Prevention - How to manage high risk patients
column16: Stepped Care -  How to decide when to step patients up to specialty care
column17: Stepped Care - How to decide when to step patients down to primary care
column18: Care Continuum -  How to manage patient care across care settings, e.g., primary care, general mental health and specialty mental health
column19: Measurement Based Care - How implementation of measurement based care will improve patient care or reduce patient risk
column25: Adjunctive services (i.e. art and recreation therapy, peer support specialists)
